\pard\qc\fs24\b ABSTRACT\par
\pard\ql\fs20
Aim: Build a lightweight, reliable single-host pipeline for near-real-time workstation telemetry and anomaly detection.\par
Method: A Python collector captures keystrokes, mouse activity, active-application context, and system metrics, hashing payloads with a Rust hasher (with a Python SHA-256 fallback) and persisting events to MySQL via JDBC (JPype/jaydebeapi) or a pure-Python connector as fallback. A Java Swing UI (using MySQL Connector/J) provides ~1 s live refresh, time-series charts, and a scheduled 5 s in-UI processor that classifies events, normalizes domain tables, and raises alerts.\par
Main result: The system delivers low-latency local ingestion, reliable domain-table population and rule-based alerting, plus one-click CSV export for downstream analysis. The combination of JDBC and Rust hashing balances performance, data integrity, and operational resilience for single-host endpoint monitoring.\par
\page

